# Orylo Design System & UI Rules

This project follows a strict "Dark Mode / Cyber / Fintech" visual identity, heavily inspired by `app/(main)/page.tsx`.
All new components and pages MUST adhere to these guidelines.

## 1. Core Visual Identity (Dark Theme Default)

- **Backgrounds**:
  - Main background: `bg-black` (or very dark zinc).
  - Cards/Surfaces: `bg-zinc-900/50` with `backdrop-blur-xl` (Glassmorphism).
  - Overlays: Subtle radial gradients (e.g., `bg-indigo-500/10 rounded-full blur-3xl`).
  - Patterns: Grid patterns (e.g., linear-gradient with transparency) for texture.

- **Borders**:
  - Subtle, semi-transparent white borders: `border-white/10` or `border-white/5`.
  - Avoid harsh solid borders.

- **Typography**:
  - Headings: White (`text-white`), bold/extrabold.
  - Body text: Zinc greys (`text-zinc-400` for secondary, `text-zinc-300` for labels).
  - Links/Accents: Indigo/Purple (`text-indigo-400`, `hover:text-indigo-300`).
  - Font: Sans-serif (Geist/Inter), clean and modern.

- **Interactive Elements (Buttons/Inputs)**:
  - **Primary Button**: White background (`bg-white`), Black text (`text-black`), subtle hover effect (`hover:bg-zinc-200`).
  - **Secondary/Ghost Button**: Transparent with light text, hover with slight white background (`hover:bg-white/5`).
  - **Inputs**: Dark background (`bg-zinc-900/50`), light border (`border-white/10`), white text, Indigo focus ring (`focus-visible:ring-indigo-500`).

## 2. Component Implementation Patterns

### Cards & Containers
When creating a card or container, use this structure:
```tsx
<Card className="w-full border-white/10 bg-zinc-900/50 backdrop-blur-xl shadow-xl">
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle className="text-white">...</CardTitle>
    <CardDescription className="text-zinc-400">...</CardDescription>
  </CardHeader>
  {/* ... */}
</Card>
```

### Inputs & Forms
```tsx
<Input 
  className="bg-zinc-900/50 border-white/10 text-white placeholder:text-zinc-500 focus-visible:ring-indigo-500"
  {...props} 
/>
```

### Animation (Framer Motion)
- Use `framer-motion` for smooth entrances (fade-in up).
- Standard transition: `initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}`.

## 3. Tailwind Utility Classes Preference
- Prefer `zinc` colors for grays (neutral cool tone).
- Prefer `indigo` or `purple` for brand accents.
- Use `backdrop-blur` heavily for depth.
- Use `opacity` modifiers for text hierarchy (`text-white` vs `text-zinc-400`).

## 4. "Do Not" Rules
- ❌ DO NOT use default white backgrounds (`bg-white`) for main pages.
- ❌ DO NOT use standard blue browser links.
- ❌ DO NOT use solid black borders.
- ❌ DO NOT use shadows without purpose (prefer glows/blurs).
